        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "FWIW [Python pathlib removes trailing slashes](https://docs.python.org/3.14/library/pathlib.html#comparison-to-the-os-and-os-path-modules):\n\n```python\n>>> import pathlib\n>>> pathlib.Path(\"foo/bar\")\nPosixPath('foo/bar')\n>>> pathlib.Path(\"foo/bar/\")\nPosixPath('foo/bar')\n>>> pathlib.Path(\"foo/bar///\")\nPosixPath('foo/bar')\n>>> _.name  # basename\n'bar'\n```\n\nPOSIX specifies that [basename(1P)](https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9799919799/utilities/basename.html) and [basename(3P)](https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9799919799/functions/basename.html#tag_17_42_06_02) shall remove trailing slashes[^1], and GNU and BSD implementations work as such.\n\n[^1]: unless the string is `//`, where return value is implementation-defined",
