        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "this is also the behavior of `vim.fn.fnamemodify`\n\n```lua\nvim.fn.fnamemodify(\"/baz.txt/\", \":t\") -- \"\"\n```\nwhich is used as the truth value in `test/functional/lua/fs_spec.lua` changing `basename` behavior would also require changing tests.\n\nI think following POSIX is the correct move here, as it is more intuitive and predictable, and should have been the target from the start IMO. \n\nonce a decision has been made, I have no problem working on this issue.",
