        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I like these functions because they're easier to understand, and I'm sure I'm not alone:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/47479757540fa3b56a48145c74eeb93db81c90f7/runtime/lua/vim/provider/health.lua#L541-L542\n\nThe only problem I see is that these path-related functions weren't designed as a standalone feature referencing quirks other languages discovered in practice, but rather as utilities meant for immediate use.\n\nLogically, you're absolutely right — it's a maintenance burden. It can easily be replaced in user configuration by using backward-compatible `fnamemodify`. But everyone still uses these functions because they've gotten used to them in other languages (including shell), so expecting the same behavior is natural.\n\nP.S. Sorry, I misclicked and accidentally closed the issue 🫠.",
            "created_at": "2026-02-27T20:14:15Z",
